                                                                      SECTION 1
 
 
                                                                   INTRODUCTION
 
 
 
 
 
       The machine readable source files available for CP-6 products all follow
       the same pattern, regardless of the product.  This SRB, therefore,
       describes the files and accounts in a general way for all CP-6 products.
 
 
 
       ________________________       Supporting Documentation
 
 
       Other than this SRB, there is no supporting documentation outside of the
       files contained in the accounts included in this element.  There are
       many HELP files and SRBs included in the element to describe the content
       and procedures.
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
       SRB_SOURCE              Supporting Documentation                     1-1
       
 
 
 
 
 
                                                                      SECTION 2
 
 
                                                            GENERAL INFORMATION
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
       ___________________       General Description
 
 
       Generally, the machine readable source for each CP-6 product is
       distributed in three accounts that are similarly named.  The
       identification of the product is inherent in the account name.  These
       account names are listed in Appendix A.
 
       The :xxxxSI account contains the source files.  The :xxxxUI contains the
       update files, which when compiled with the SI files will recreate the
       product as released.  If there is no matching :xxxxUI account, then the
       product can be created wholly from the source.  The :xxxxMSC account
       contains the JCL and control files needed to compile and LINK the
       product.  The :xxxxMSC account contains HELP files which describe the
       JCL and other files.  All HELP files have the same naming convention:
       item_HELP for files describing "item".  The MSC account is included as
       an example of how LADC creates the products and should be modified by
       the user, as necessary.
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
       SRB_SOURCE                 General Description                       2-1
       
 
 
 
 
 
                                                                      SECTION 3
 
 
                                                      INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS
 
 
 
 
 
       The release media is an EFT tape set.  Create the accounts required, as
       specified in Appendix A, and restore the accounts from the EFT tape.
 
       Copy ?_HELP.:xxxxMSC to the line printer.
 
       The tools to be used in the compilations and LINKs are all in account
        .X and .:TOOL.  Some examples are FUMBLE, LISTER, EDGEMARK, and FORMAT.
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
       SRB_SOURCE              INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS                    3-1
       
 
 
 
 
 
